Feature Plan: VenueForMoviesVC expanded-list redesign with category + screening date (UIKit)

Objective
- Refresh `VenueForMoviesVC` to a polished expanded-list style for the Home -> Venues -> MapView flow.
- Show one row per movie item with richer metadata.
- Include category and screening date in each row.
- Keep existing navigation behavior and endpoint contracts.

Constraints
- UIKit-only implementation.
- No backend tasks in this feature.
- No endpoint contract/header/payload changes.
- Use existing movies + screening-date endpoint responses.

Role ownership
- Primary iOS implementation: `@ios-dev`
- Contract compatibility review: `@backend-dev`
- Manual regression verification: `@testing-engineer`

Target files
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/VenueForMoviesVC.swift`
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/ListViewCell.swift` (if reusable row style is shared)
- `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/prototypes/venueformoviesvc-redesign.prototype.html`
- `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/speckit.swiftuifeatures.venueformoviesvc-redesign.specify`
- `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/speckit.swiftuifeatures.venueformoviesvc-redesign.tasks`

High-level architecture
1. List visual refresh
   - Shift to expanded-list visual hierarchy and spacing.
   - Keep vertical one-row-per-item rendering.
2. Metadata enrichment
   - Bind `category` from existing movies endpoint data.
   - Bind `screeningDate` from existing screening-date endpoint data.
   - Provide `N/A` / `TBA` fallback labels when missing.
3. Flow continuity
   - Preserve navigation and selection contracts currently used by map/venues flow.
4. No-backend guardrail
   - Explicitly avoid backend endpoint changes or new backend tasks.
5. Validation and diagnostics
   - Verify mapping counts and fallback usage without logging sensitive headers/tokens.

Interaction behavior
- User reaches VenueForMovies list via Home -> Venues -> Map flow.
- User sees expanded-list rows with title + category + screening date.
- User can select rows and continue with existing navigation behavior.

Verification strategy
- Visual verify expanded-list style and readable hierarchy.
- Verify category and screening date are shown in row cells.
- Verify fallback labels display when data missing.
- Verify no backend changes are required.
- Verify navigation flow remains intact.

Definition of done
- Speckit artifacts (`.specify`, `.plan`, `.tasks`, prototype) are complete and aligned.
- Prototype clearly shows category and screening date in each list row.
- No backend task scope is introduced.

